275
00:13:36,049 --> 00:13:38,818
No, you mustn't!

276
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:42,388
One day, Moo will
take over your world!

277
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:46,259
Give us the stone
and you can join us!

278
00:13:46,259 --> 00:13:48,561
Never.

279
00:13:48,561 --> 00:13:53,032
Then you can deal
with the wrath of Moo.

280
00:13:53,032 --> 00:13:55,368
For Moo!

281
00:13:55,368 --> 00:13:58,171
(growling)

282
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:04,877
♪

283
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:07,480
(screeching)

284
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,716
♪

285
00:14:09,716 --> 00:14:11,984
(crashing)

286
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:19,225
♪

287
00:14:19,225 --> 00:14:21,394
(evil laughter)

288
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:36,542
♪

289
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,745
Is it safe?

290
00:14:38,745 --> 00:14:42,215
I think so.

291
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:45,084
No!

292
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:46,853
(gasping)

293
00:14:46,853 --> 00:14:49,622
Grandfather, Grandfather!

294
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:51,691
What happened?

295
00:14:51,691 --> 00:14:54,394
Holly, Naga came,

296
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:57,430
and the others are...

297
00:14:57,430 --> 00:15:01,601
lost disks now.

298
00:15:01,601 --> 00:15:03,669
No, it can't be.

299
00:15:03,669 --> 00:15:05,438
It can't be!

300
00:15:05,438 --> 00:15:08,508
Moo's forces were too strong.

301
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:12,945
Our good friends
are gone forever.

302
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:14,981
Forgive me, for I was the one

303
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:17,483
who sent your father into exile.

304
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:21,754
His power over the
magic stone was so great

305
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:23,856
that it frightened me.

306
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:25,825
I thought such
power would one day

307
00:15:25,825 --> 00:15:28,261
bring disaster to our village.

308
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:30,630
‐Grandfather.
‐Holly,

309
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:33,833
if he had been here to
fight against Moo's forces,

310
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:37,003
things would've been different.

311
00:15:37,003 --> 00:15:40,740
‐Do you have the bag I gave you?
‐Right here, Grandfather.

312
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,241
Open it.

313
00:15:42,241 --> 00:15:43,810
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

314
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:45,812
♪

315
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:47,079
‐The stone!
‐The stone!

316
00:15:47,079 --> 00:15:50,550
You have your
father's powers, Holly.

317
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:54,921
You must take the magic stone
and find the mystery disk

318
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:57,623
that contains the
ancient Phoenix.

319
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:00,159
What's a Phoenix?

320
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:02,428
Only the Phoenix has the power

321
00:16:02,428 --> 00:16:05,498
to revive the lost monsters.

322
00:16:05,498 --> 00:16:09,268
But Grandfather, I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

323
00:16:09,268 --> 00:16:13,105
If the legend is true,
the Phoenix will revive

324
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:15,608
the lost monsters, and transform

325
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:18,411
the bad monsters into good ones.

326
00:16:18,411 --> 00:16:22,482
It's the only hope we have
of defeating the evil Moo.

327
00:16:22,482 --> 00:16:24,617
♪

328
00:16:24,617 --> 00:16:26,886
I'm counting on you.

329
00:16:26,886 --> 00:16:31,424
♪

330
00:16:31,424 --> 00:16:34,126
We're all counting on you.

331
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:36,796
♪

332
00:16:36,796 --> 00:16:39,265
(birds chirping)

333
00:16:39,265 --> 00:16:42,134
♪

334
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:44,504
(gasping)

335
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:47,874
♪

336
00:16:47,874 --> 00:16:51,644
The Phoenix!

337
00:16:51,644 --> 00:16:55,381
The magic stone has always
led me in the right direction,

338
00:16:55,381 --> 00:16:59,252
from the very first.

339
00:16:59,252 --> 00:17:00,853
We must go.

340
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:03,656
Great, I'm with you!

341
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:06,359
And so Suezo and I set off,

342
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:09,262
going wherever the magic
stone told us to go.

343
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:12,465
(rain pattering)

344
00:17:12,465 --> 00:17:15,201
Ohhh.

345
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:18,504
So that's why you're
on the journey, huh?

346
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:22,041
Hey, did you ever meet
up with your dad again?

347
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,676
Mm‐mm.

348
00:17:23,676 --> 00:17:27,179
Genki.

349
00:17:27,179 --> 00:17:30,049
And I vowed I'd never cry again.

350
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,184
‐Holly.
‐'chi.

351
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:34,720
♪

352
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,189
(indistinct remarks)

353
00:17:37,189 --> 00:17:41,827
♪

354
00:17:41,827 --> 00:17:45,431
Genki, at times like this,
you have to lighten the mood.

355
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:48,367
‐Hare is right!
‐For once.

356
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:50,570
Hey!

357
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:54,040
Ladies and gentlemen,
the amazing Genki!

358
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:55,474
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

359
00:17:55,474 --> 00:17:56,909
‐Genki!
‐Genki!

360
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:01,180
Ta‐da, and now I'm going
to sing you a song.

361
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:04,884
♪ It's raining, it's
pouring, Suezo is snoring ♪

362
00:18:04,884 --> 00:18:06,519
♪ He fell in a puddle
and got in a muddle

363
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:08,654
but at least he
won't be boring ♪

364
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:11,324
Yeah, all right, this is fun,
come on you guys, join in!

365
00:18:11,324 --> 00:18:13,259
It's so cool, yeah, all right!

366
00:18:13,259 --> 00:18:15,027
He's gaga.

367
00:18:15,027 --> 00:18:17,797
One more time,
everybody, jump and sing!

368
00:18:17,797 --> 00:18:19,966
♪ While the rain comes
down and hits the ground

369
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,601
with a splashy sound ♪

370
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:23,703
Yeah, all right, yeah!

371
00:18:23,703 --> 00:18:25,671
♪ Everybody jumps
and dances around ♪

372
00:18:25,671 --> 00:18:27,306
Mocchi!

373
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:29,208
♪ The drops go bloop,
the flowers droop ♪

374
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:31,143
♪ The sun comes out, we all go

375
00:18:31,143 --> 00:18:32,878
doodly‐oodly, scroodly‐noodly ♪

376
00:18:32,878 --> 00:18:34,981
♪ Doodly‐poodly, puddly‐wuddly ♪

377
00:18:34,981 --> 00:18:37,049
♪ Duddly‐fuddly, woozy‐woozy ♪

378
00:18:37,049 --> 00:18:39,285
♪ Woodle‐woozy,
doozy‐doozy‐doo ♪

379
00:18:39,285 --> 00:18:40,886
♪ Doo‐doo‐doo‐doo‐doo‐doo ♪

380
00:18:40,886 --> 00:18:42,188
Gaga.

381
00:18:42,188 --> 00:18:44,590
Golem sing too.

382
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,125
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

383
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:50,429
♪

384
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:52,598
'chi!

385
00:18:52,598 --> 00:18:54,500
Tiger, Suezo, Hare!

386
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,735
Come on, it's fun!

387
00:18:55,735 --> 00:18:59,405
‐It's just silly!
‐Shall we?

388
00:18:59,405 --> 00:19:00,439
Why not?

389
00:19:00,439 --> 00:19:03,409
Career's have been made on less.

390
00:19:03,409 --> 00:19:04,577
Gaga too.

391
00:19:04,577 --> 00:19:06,545
♪ Gabba‐gabba, gabba‐gabba,
